In a developing country struggling with electricity generation and the scarcity of water, maths and physics are not enforced as priority subjects at our schools. Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga has instead pre-occupied herself with exonerating the government from improving dilapidated rural and township schools. What’s up, Angie? Why are science subjects being phased out at some schools in the country while we so desperately need scientists? Ag maan, go fly a kite! Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here. 